---
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Link from "@components/Link.astro";
import { MANIFOLD } from "@consts";
---

<PageLayout title={MANIFOLD.TITLE} description={MANIFOLD.DESCRIPTION}>
  <Container>
    <div class="space-y-10">
      <div class="animate font-semibold text-black dark:text-white text-xl">
        Manifold
      </div>

      <p class="animate text-sm italic opacity-85">
        Hi, this is Rabindra! You'are welcome to contour across my manifold.
      </p>

      <p class="animate text-sm opacity-75">
        This is the surface, the trajectory, the coordinates of — who I am and where I've been.
      </p>

      <article class="animate space-y-6">

        <!-- Section 1: Johnson & Johnson -->
        <hr class="border-black/10 dark:border-white/10" />

        <h2 class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white text-lg">
          <span class="opacity-50 mr-1">§1</span> Johnson & Johnson — Data Scientist
        </h2>

        <p class="font-serif leading-relaxed">
          I currently work as a Principal Data Scientist at Johnson & Johnson, where I lead AI/ML initiatives within corporate functions to drive innovation through generative AI and data science. My work focuses on developing scalable generative AI and machine learning solutions to enhance employee experience and corporate functions.
        </p>

        <!-- Section 2: Zoetis -->
        <hr class="border-black/10 dark:border-white/10" />

        <h2 class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white text-lg">
          <span class="opacity-50 mr-1">§2</span> Zoetis — Data Scientist
        </h2>

        <p class="font-serif leading-relaxed">
          Before J&J, I worked as a Senior Scientist in Data Science at Zoetis (2019–2022), the world's leading animal health company. My work centered on precision animal health — building predictive models and analytical solutions for livestock health, productivity, and sustainability under Zoetis's continuum-of-care framework of predict, prevent, detect, and treat.
        </p>

        <p class="font-serif leading-relaxed">
          I developed and deployed machine learning products for on-farm decision-making — disease risk prediction, reproductive success modeling, and productivity analytics — leveraging phenotypic, genotypic, diagnostic, sensor (time-series), and weather data. I partnered closely with animal scientists, veterinarians, and clinicians to build and validate solutions in commercial farm settings.
        </p>

        <p class="font-serif leading-relaxed">
          I also worked on computer vision solutions for automatic animal behavior, health events tracking using 2D and 3D camera feeds, and automated blood smear analysis in companion animals for differential blood cell counting from super-resolution pathological slide scans.
        </p>

        <!-- Section 3: The Academic Arc -->
        <hr class="border-black/10 dark:border-white/10" />

        <h2 class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white text-lg">
          <span class="opacity-50 mr-1">§3</span> The Academic Arc
        </h2>

        <p class="font-serif leading-relaxed">
          My physics journey began in Nepal with a BSc, continued in India for an MSc, and culminated in a PhD in Physics from the University of Nebraska–Lincoln. Along the way, I focused on condensed matter physics, spintronics, and quantum information processing.
        </p>

        <p class="font-serif leading-relaxed">
          My doctoral work centered on theoretical and computational spintronics — the dynamics of magnetic skyrmions in chiral magnets. I built large-scale micromagnetic simulations, studied emergent magnetic phenomena, and used early deep learning methods to classify magnetic phases. Earlier work explored quantum entanglement and information capacities in multipartite quantum systems. Those years shaped my approach to modeling complex systems, a thread that still runs through everything I do today.
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3 font-serif text-sm">
          <li>
            <Link href="https://journals.aps.org/pra/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevA.87.032336" external>
              "Maximally-dense-coding-capable quantum states"
            </Link>, R Nepal, R Prabhu, A Sen, U Sen, <em>Physical Review A</em> 87 (3), 032336, 2013
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://journals.aps.org/prb/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevB.93.064428" external>
              "Stability of skyrmion lattices and symmetries of quasi-two-dimensional chiral magnets"
            </Link>, U Güngördü, R Nepal, OA Tretiakov, K Belashchenko, AA Kovalev, <em>Physical Review B</em> 93 (6), 064428, 2016
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://pubs.aip.org/aip/apl/article/112/11/112404/34636" external>
              "Magnetic skyrmion bubble motion driven by surface acoustic waves"
            </Link>, R Nepal, U Güngördü, AA Kovalev, <em>Applied Physics Letters</em> 112 (11), 112404, 2018
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://pubs.aip.org/aip/apl/article/112/5/052402/36096" external>
              "SAW assisted domain wall motion in Co/Pt multilayers"
            </Link>, W Edrington, U Singh, MA Dominguez, JR Alexander, R Nepal, ... <em>Applied Physics Letters</em> 112 (5), 2018
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://journals.aps.org/prmaterials/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevMaterials.2.124401" external>
              "Boundary twists, instabilities, and creation of skyrmions and antiskyrmions"
            </Link>, A Raeliarijaona, R Nepal, AA Kovalev, <em>Physical Review Materials</em> 2 (12), 124401, 2018
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://journals.aps.org/prb/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevB.99.094111" external>
              "Valley-dependent Lorentz force and Aharonov-Bohm phase in strained graphene junction"
            </Link>, S Prabhakar, R Nepal, R Melnik, AA Kovalev, <em>Physical Review B</em> 99 (9), 094111, 2019
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://journals.aps.org/prb/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevB.104.064417" external>
              "Regular and in-plane skyrmions and antiskyrmions from boundary instabilities"
            </Link>, S Sandhoefner, A Raeliarijaona, R Nepal, D Snyder-Tinoco, AA Kovalev, <em>Physical Review B</em> 104 (6), 064417, 2021
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://journals.aps.org/pra/abstract/10.1103/PhysRevA.90.042326" external>
              "Parafermion stabilizer codes"
            </Link>, U Güngördü, R Nepal, AA Kovalev, <em>Physical Review A</em> 90 (4), 042326, 2014
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://www.proquest.com/openview/87b41400f653ebb3abab21784975b37d/1?pq-origsite=gscholar&cbl=18750&diss=y" external>
              "Stability, Dynamics, and Nucleation of Magnetic Skyrmions"
            </Link>, Nepal, Rabindra, <em>Dissertation</em>, 2018
          </li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="border-black/10 dark:border-white/10" />

        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black dark:text-white text-base">Connect</h3>

        <div class="flex justify-center gap-6 mt-4">
          <Link href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nepalrabindra/" external aria-label="LinkedIn">
            LinkedIn
          </Link>
          <Link href="https://github.com/rnepal2" external aria-label="GitHub">
            GitHub
          </Link>
          <Link href="https://x.com/ccRabindra" external aria-label="Twitter/X">
            Twitter/X
          </Link>
          <Link href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=Z8tzkKEAAAAJ&hl=en" external aria-label="Google Scholar">
            Google Scholar
          </Link>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Container>
</PageLayout>
